  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel the chorizo and slice into rounds, roughly half a centimetre\nthick. Get a large saucepan over a high heat. Drizzle in some olive\noil, then scrape in the chorizo. Leave to fry."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, remove the peppers from the jar with a fork, roughly\nslice and add them to the pan along with the unpeeled garlic,\ncrushing the cloves into the pan. Add the Cajun seasoning and\nstir, cooking for a further minute."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Open the tins of beans, drain the liquid in a sieve and then add to\nthe pan. Pour in the passata. Season with salt and black pepper\nand give everything a good mix. Bring the chilli to the boil and let\nit bubble away while you make the guac."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the guacamole. Cut one lime in half and the other into four\nwedges. Halve and pit the avocados and scoop out the flesh into\na small bowl. Squeeze over the juice from the lime halves, season\nwith salt and black pepper and then smash up with a fork.\nGuac – done."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tear the coriander over the chilli and serve at the table with the\nbowl of guac, some Cheddar cheese for topping and the lime\nwedges for squeezing over."
    }
  ],
